<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 of 16 March 1987 on the common organization of the market in wine (1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1592/96 (2), and in particular Articles 32 (5) and 83 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 16. m&auml;rtsi 1987. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 veinituru &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1592/96, eriti selle artikli 32 l&otilde;iget 5 ja artiklit 83, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the forward estimate drawn up for the 1996/97 wine year indicates that the quantities of table wine available at the beginning of the wine year exceed by more than four months' supply those normally used up over the year; whereas the conditions for authorization of long-term storage contracts specified in Article 32 (4) of Regulation (EEC) No 822/87 are therefore met; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1996/97 veiniaastaks koostatud eelhinnang n&auml;itab, et veiniaasta alguses saadaolevad lauaveinikogused &uuml;letavad keskmisi aasta jooksul kasutatavad varusid rohkem kui nelja kuu varude v&otilde;rra; m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 822/87 artikli 32 l&otilde;ikes 4 m&auml;&auml;ratletud tingimused pikaajaliste laolepingute s&otilde;lmimise lubamiseks on seega t&auml;idetud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the abovementioned forward estimate indicates the existence of surpluses of all types of table wine and of table wines which stand in close economic relationship to those types of table wine; whereas it is necessary by the same token to open this possibility for grape must, concentrated grape must and rectified concentrated grape must; </inglise>
<eesti> eespool mainitud eelhinnang n&auml;itab k&otilde;ikide lauaveinit&uuml;&uuml;pide ja nende lauaveinit&uuml;&uuml;pidega tihedas majanduslikus seoses olevate lauaveinide &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;ki; k&otilde;nealuste veinit&uuml;&uuml;pide puhul tuleks seep&auml;rast ette n&auml;ha v&otilde;imalus s&otilde;lmida pikaajalisi lepinguid; samadel p&otilde;hjustel tuleks seda v&otilde;imaldada ka viinamarjavirde, kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirde ja puhastatud kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirde puhul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the market for must and concentrated must for grape juice production is expanding and to promote uses of vine products other than winemaking permission should be granted for must and concentrated grape must placed under a storage contract covered by Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1059/83 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1262/96 (4), that is intended for grape juice production to be sold from the fifth month of the contract onwards on simple notification by the producer to the intervention agency; whereas to promote export of these products this same possibility should apply; </inglise>
<eesti> viinamarjamahla valmistamiseks kasutatava viinamarjavirde ja kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirde turg laieneb; soodustamaks viinamarjatoodete kasutamist muudel kui veinivalmistamise eesm&auml;rkidel, tuleks viinamarjavirde ja kontsentreeritud viinamarjavirde puhul, mille kohta on s&otilde;lmitud laoleping m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1059/83 alusel (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1262/96) ja mis on ette n&auml;htud viinamarjamahla valmistamiseks, anda luba nende m&uuml;&uuml;giks alates viiendast kuust p&auml;rast lepingu s&otilde;lmimist, kui tootja esitab selleks sekkumisasutusele taotluse; nende toodete v&auml;ljaveo soodustamiseks tuleks kohaldada sama v&otilde;imalust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Wine, </inglise>
